WHAT IS THIS FILE
The certified computing profile for the NVIDIA GeForce RTX 5090 GPU,
built on the Blackwell architecture. It defines the CUDA core array,
5th-generation Tensor Core AI throughput, 4th-generation RT Core ray
tracing acceleration, GDDR7 memory subsystem, and DLSS 4 Multi Frame
Generation pipeline.

WHY IT EXISTS
The RTX 5090 is the reference GPU for real-time path tracing, AI denoising,
and neural rendering in GIOP workstations. Its silicon must be modeled as
formulas so that rendering and AI inference times are predictable.

HOW IT WORKS
CUDA Core Compute (FP32):
  TFLOPS_FP32 = (CUDA_cores * 2 * f_gpu) / 1e12
  = (21,760 * 2 * 2.52e9) / 1e12 ≈ 109.7 TFLOPS[reference:13]

Tensor Core AI Throughput (FP8, 5th Gen):
  AI_TOPS = 3,352 (marketed by NVIDIA)[reference:14]
  FP4 sparse throughput ≈ 2× FP8 = ~6,700 TOPS.
  The tensor core performs matrix multiply-accumulate:
    D = A × B + C
  where A (M×K), B (K×N) are FP8 matrices, accumulated in FP32.

RT Core (4th Gen):
  Ray_triangle_intersections_per_sec = RT_cores * f_rt * ops_per_cycle
  ≈ 192 * 2.52e9 * 4 ≈ 1.94 Tera-rays/s (peak).
  BVH traversal is hardware-accelerated; two-level BVH for dynamic scenes.

Memory Bandwidth (GDDR7, 512-bit):
  BW = (bus_width_bytes * f_data * PAM3_efficiency) / 1e9
  = (64 * 28e9 * 1.5) / 1e9 ≈ 2,688 GB/s (PAM3 signaling, 28 Gbps per pin)
  Total VRAM: 32 GB.[reference:15]

Power (TDP):
  P_total = P_CUDA + P_Tensor + P_RT + P_memory
  TDP: 575 W. P_CUDA dominates at ~400 W under full FP32 load.

DLSS 4 Multi Frame Generation:
  Generates up to 3 interpolated frames per rendered frame using optical
  flow and a transformer-based frame generation network running on tensor
  cores. Effective frame rate multiplier: up to 8×.

GIOP Integration:
  GIOP's neural denoiser (Kingdom 07) targets the RTX 5090 tensor core
  array. The certified ODT renderer queries available AI TOPS and selects
  the DLSS quality preset accordingly.

WHERE IT IS DEPLOYED
- GIOP mastering workstations, real-time path tracing, AI denoising,
  neural compression.
- Virtual production (Unreal Engine + GIOP ODT).

WHO USES IT
L2 Engineers building GIOP render farms; L3 Colorists working in real-
time HDR grading environments.

WHAT PROBLEM IT SOLVES
Provides the exact TFLOPS, TOPS, and bandwidth formulas so that any GIOP
rendering or AI task can be scheduled with known completion time and
power cost.

